This paper deals with the problem of error probability in multiple access channels, which is a topic in information theory and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves coding theory and communication systems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper uses mathematical analysis and probability theory, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
